etymologies: modern Latin, from Latin, from Greek nautilos, literally ‘sailor’

definitions: a cephalopod mollusk with a light external spiral shell and numerous short tentacles around the mouth. Nautiluses swim with the buoyant gas-filled shell upright and descend to greater depths during the day.

notes.text: Genus Nautilus, the only surviving genus of the subclass Nautiloidea: several species, in particular the common chambered nautilus (Nautilus pompilius) of the Indo-Pacific, with a shell that is white with brownish bands on the outside and lined with mother-of-pearl on the inside

shortDefinitions: cephalopod mollusc with light external spiral shell
